<h2>Dear New Line Cinema,</h2>
The Stephen King novel, The Long Walk, has been my research project for the past year.<br>
<br>
I have read it twenty times, sharing my knowledge on my <a href="TheLongWalk.aspx">web site</a> and <a href="TheLongWalk-YouTube.aspx">YouTube Channel</a>, dedicated solely to The Long Walk.<br>
<br>
I am offering my <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4zLoxyMCZi0" _target="blank">knowledge and expertise</a> to help improve or promote <a href="TheLongWalk-movie.aspx">the movie</a>.

<h3>Ways I can help:</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Give my feedback on the screen-play</li>
    <li>Give my feedback on early cuts of the movie</li>
    <li>Help with the web site (I'm a <a href="http://www.linkedin.com/in/patrickcoston">web-developer</a>)</li>
    <li>Create a mobile App to simulate The Long Walk to gamify exercise (I'm a <a href="http://www.linkedin.com/in/patrickcoston">software developer</a>)</li>
    <li>Promote the movie by walking the 440-mile route while making daily vlogs</li>
    <li>Help organize an actual long walk for charity with 100 people (picked randomly from lottery) of the 440-mile route</li>
    <li>Help organize a 24-hour long walk for charity (which could leverage the app)</li>
    <li>Help organize long walks between cities in the book, like Limestone to Caribou, or Lewiston to Freeport</li>
</ol>

<h3>Other ideas to promote the movie:</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Toys and action figures like <a href="https://www.funko.com/">Funko POP!</a> figures of the major characters</li>
    <li>Chess board: Soldiers pawns, Garraty King, Jan Queen, Stebbins Rook, McVries Bishop, Barkovitch Knight</li>
    <li>Social media like Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, Snapchat, Reddit, YouTube</li>
    <li>Have the actors do a fun-walk of 10 miles</li>
    <li>New cover featuring actors</li>
    <li>The Long Walk comic</li>
    <li>The Long Walk TV series. 3 seasons for past, present and future</li>
    <li>Hard-cover printing</li>
</ol>

<h3>Here are the results of my research:</h3>

<ol>
<li>Defined the <a href="TheLongWalk-Timeline.aspx">timeline</a> for the book</li>
<li>Calculated the exact <a href="TheLongWalk-Route.aspx">route</a> based on the timeline</li>
<li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8MhHH_4R9i8&list=PLxKs0b5kesoa7meYMavrDSBeoxDTSI1NY">Road tripped</a> the route</li>
<li>Defined <a href="TheLongWalk-Rules.aspx">the rules</a> in great details</li>
<li>Reviewed <a href="TheLongWalk-VideoReviews.aspx">every long-walk YouTube video</a> (in English)</li>
<li>Designed a <a href="TheLongWalk-Challenge.aspx">cardio-workout</a> based on the long walk rules</li>
<li>Updated <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Long_Walk">Wikipedia</a>
    and the <a href="http://stephenking.wikia.com/wiki/The_Long_Walk">Stephen King Wiki</a></li>
<li>Write my own fan-fiction, like The Long Walk in the year <a href="TheLongWalk2020.htm">2020</a></li>
<li>Hired an artist to create the most accurate <a href="TheLongWalk-Art.aspx">fan-art</a></li>
<li>and so much more!</li>
</ol>
